title: Virginia Peak (Nevada)
text: Virginia Peak is the highest <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in the <a href="Pah%20Rah%20Range">Pah Rah Range</a> of <a href="Washoe%20County%2C%20Nevada">Washoe County</a> in <a href="Nevada">Nevada</a>, United States. It is the most <a href="topographic%20prominence">topographically prominent</a> peak in Washoe County and ranks thirty-sixth among the most topographically prominent peaks in Nevada. The peak is on public land administered by the <a href="Bureau%20of%20Land%20Management">Bureau of Land Management</a> and thus has no access restrictions. A <a href="National%20Weather%20Service">National Weather Service</a> <a href="NEXRAD">NEXRAD</a> <a href="Weather%20radar">doppler weather radar</a> station is located on the summit.
